This script quantifies how EEG signal power is distributed across frequencies using power spectral density (PSD) estimates derived from raw EEG via Welchâ€™s method. It computes absolute spectral power to characterise the overall spectral shape, slope, and dominant frequency components of the signal, and relative (baseline-normalised) PSD to express frequency-specific changes in power with respect to an eyes-closed resting baseline.

The analysis operates at two levels: continuous frequency spectra and band-integrated power across canonical EEG bands. This allows inspection of broadband spectral structure as well as band-specific contributions. Channel-wise PSDs are summarised using robust statistics (median and interquartile range), enabling assessment of central tendencies and spatial variability without undue influence from outlier electrodes.
